nd which are a deep orange colour and look a bit like a tiny flat disc. We have a glossary page on lentils which may help a little more&nbsp;http://www.bbcgoodfood.com/glossary/lentils. Hope this helps, let us know how you get on or if you need more information. &nbsp;</div></div></div></div></div> </article></div></div></div><h2 class="element-invisible">Pages</h2><ul class="pager unstyled horizontal-elements"><li class="pager-current first">1</li><li class="pager-item"><a title="Go to page 2" href="/recipes/2089/spiced-carrot-and-lentil-soup?page=1#c">2</a></li><li class="pager-item"><a title="Go to page 3" href="/recipes/2089/spiced-carrot-and-lentil-soup?page=2#c">3</a></li><li class="pager-next bg-turquoise-safe last"><a title="Go to next page" href="/recipes/2089/spiced-carrot-and-lentil-soup?page=1#c">next </a></li></ul></div></div><div id="fragment-tip" class="section-comments__single-tab-content"><div class="view view-comment-views-comment-ajax view-id-comment_views_comment_ajax view-display-id-tip_page view-dom-id-386cd33dd6e8f0fc64af87189b02f43e"><div class="view-content"><div><div id="comment-wrapper-1046001"><a id="comment-1046001"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"><div class="user-picture"> <img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/avatar/public/pictures/picture-6856766-1520255127.jpg?itok=ms_G15l0" width="40" height="40" alt="Rochelle Beech&#039;s picture" title="Rochelle Beech&#039;s picture" /></div></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">Rochelle Beech</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 5th Mar, 2018</div> </header><div class="comment__rating-and-report-wrapper"><div class="comment__rating"><div class="rate-widget rate-widget-fivestar clear-block rate-processed"><div class="fivestar-bbcgoodfood"><div class="clearfix fivestar-widget-static fivestar-widget-static-vote fivestar-widget-static-5"><div class="star star-1 star-odd star-first"><sp